</P>
<P>
-- CAMP PENDLETON, California -- Hearing to reopen for Marine
officer charged in Haditha deaths. Moved.
</P>
<P>
Artist in replica antique submersible in New York startles
authorities; near Queen Mary 2
</P>
<P>
NEW YORK -- An artist manning a replica of a 200-year-old
submersible caused a scare after police found the strange-looking
vessel foundering in a security zone near the docked Queen Mary
2, authorities said.  SUBMARINE. Moved. By Pat Milton.
</P>
<P>
LATIN AMERICA:
</P>
<P>
Mexican researchers locate what may be funeral chambers of Aztec
emperor
</P>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- Mexican archaeologists using ground-penetrating
radar have detected underground chambers that they believe
contain the remains of Emperor Ahuizotl, who ruled the Aztecs
when Columbus landed in the New World. It would be the first tomb
of an Aztec ruler ever found.  TOMB. Developing. By Mark
Stevenson. AP Photos. AP Graphic AZTEC TOMB. AP Photos.
</P>
<P>
On the road with Sean Penn and Venezuela's Hugo Chavez
</P>
<P>
LA GRITA, Venezuela -- Aboard the presidential jet, a grinning
Hugo Chavez puts a hand on Sean Penn's shoulder, praises his
acting and adds: "And he's anti-Bush!" The Venezuelan president
revels in his role as host to the Hollywood star as they fly
across the country and travel through the countryside in a jeep
with Chavez at the wheel.  AND HUGO. By Ian James. With AP
Photos.
</P>
